'''Arda Güler''' ({{IPA|tr|aɾˈda ˈɟylæɾ|-|Arda Güler - Name.ogg}}; born 25 February 2005) is a Turkish professional footballer who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for {{Spanish football updater|Real Madrid}} club [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]]. He is regarded as one of the best young players in the world.<ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4" /><ref name=":5" />

Güler began his senior career with the Turkish club [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] in 2021, where he won the [[Turkish Cup]] in 2023. In 2023, Güler signed with Real Madrid. In his inaugural season with the Spanish giants, he won the [[List of Spanish football champions|La Liga]] and the [[UEFA Champions League]].

At the international level, Güler made his senior debut for Turkey in 2022. He was a member of the squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]] and played a key role in the team's run to the quarter-finals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 June 2025 |title=Arda Guler: 'Turkish Messi' ready to replace Luka Modric at Real Madrid |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c15wnxw2ld4o |access-date=5 October 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=19 June 2024 |title=Arda Güler praised in the press after Turkey's EURO win |url=https://hispanatolia.com/en/arda-guler-praised-in-the-press-after-turkeys-euro-win/ |access-date=5 October 2025 |language=en}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Güler started his youth career at [[Ankara]]-based club [[Gençlerbirliği S.K.|Gençlerbirliği]], in 2014.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news |date=15 December 2022 |title=Son dakika! Fenerbahçe, Arda Güler için Gençlerbirliği ile anlaştı! İşte ödenecek rakam... |trans-title=Breaking news! Fenerbahçe has agreed with Gençlerbirliği for Arda Güler! Here is the amount to be paid... |language=tr |work=Habertürk |url=https://www.haberturk.com/fenerbahce-arda-guler-icin-genclerbirligi-ile-anlasti-iste-odenecek-rakam-3547692-spor |access-date=31 January 2023 |archive-date=31 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230131172416/https://www.haberturk.com/fenerbahce-arda-guler-icin-genclerbirligi-ile-anlasti-iste-odenecek-rakam-3547692-spor |url-status=live }}</ref> Arda Güler was discovered by Turkish powerhouse [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] on 20 February 2019, when he was only 13 years old, and was included in the youth squad. Güler, who has played in all of the [[Fenerbahçe S.K. Academy|Fenerbahçe youth teams]] including U-15, U-16 and U-19, first started playing for the Fenerbahçe U-15 team in the 2018-19 season, and was taken to the U-16 team in 2020 and the U19 team in 2021. He contributed 7 goals and 4 assists in 18 matches for the Fenerbahçe U-19 team. He made 3 goals and 1 assist in the U-19 Play-Off quarterfinal match, and thus attracted attention as the top scorer in that season's Play-Off.

In July 2021, Güler began waiting for his place in the [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]]’s first team.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-07-06 |title=Arda Güler kimdir, nereli, hangi takımlarda oynadı? Arda Güler'in kariyeri hakkında bilgiler |trans-title=Who is Arda Güler, where is he from, and which teams has he played for? Information about Arda Güler's career. |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/arda-guler-kimdir-nereli-hangi-takimlarda-oynadi-arda-gulerin-kariyeri-hakkinda-bilgiler-42294453 |access-date=29 September 2024 |website=www.hurriyet.com.tr |language=tr}}</ref><ref name=":0" />

===Fenerbahçe===
[[File:Arda Güler (2021-22 Süper Lig) - Resim3 (cropped).png|thumb|upright|Güler with [[Fenerbahçe S.K.|Fenerbahçe]] in 2021]]
Güler signed a two-and-a-half-year-long professional contract with [[Fenerbahçe S.K.|Fenerbahçe]] on 13 January 2021.<ref name="2020–21 professional contract">{{cite news|title=Altyapı futbolcumuz Arda Güler'le profesyonel sözleşme imzalandı|trans-title=A professional contract has been signed with our youth player Arda Güler|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol-altyapi/2021/1/altyapi-futbolcumuz-arda-guler-le-profesyonel-sozlesme-imzalandi|publisher=[[Fenerbahçe S.K.]]|date=13 January 2021|access-date=20 February 2021|language=tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210820080828/https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol-altyapi/2021/1/altyapi-futbolcumuz-arda-guler-le-profesyonel-sozlesme-imzalandi|archive-date=20 August 2021}}</ref> He was considered as a wonderkid and seen as a big prospect for the future.<ref>{{Cite news |date=19 April 2022 |title=Arda Guler: The Turkish wonderkid the whole of Europe wants to sign |work=Goal (website) |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/arda-guler-turkish-wonderkid-whole-europe-want-sign/blt7b158033c7eb2c97 |access-date=29 January 2023 |archive-date=19 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220419112711/https://www.goal.com/en/news/arda-guler-turkish-wonderkid-whole-europe-want-sign/blt7b158033c7eb2c97 |url-status=live }}</ref>

====2021–22 season====
Güler made his senior debut as a substitute player against Finnish club [[Helsingin Jalkapalloklubi|HJK]] in the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round|play-off round]] encounter of the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League]]. Held at [[Şükrü Saracoğlu Stadium]] on 19 August 2021, it ended 1–0 for Fenerbahçe.<ref name="2021 Senior Debut">{{cite news|title=Fenerbahçe (TUR) 1–0 HJK (Finland)|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2033103--fenerbahce-vs-hjk/matchinfo/?iv=true|publisher=[[UEFA]]|date=19 August 2021|access-date=20 August 2021|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210820080047/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2033103--fenerbahce-vs-hjk/matchinfo/?iv=true|archive-date=20 August 2021}}</ref> In his first [[Süper Lig]] match three days later, he provided the assist that let [[Miha Zajc]] score a goal at the 89th minute of the 2–0 victory over [[Antalyaspor]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Fenerbahçe 2–0 Fraport TAV Antalyaspor|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2021-tr/8/fenerbahce-2-0-%C2%A0fraport-tav-antalyaspor|publisher=Fenerbahçe S.K.|date=22 August 2021|access-date=27 April 2024|language=tr|archive-date=26 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240426233458/https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2021-tr/8/fenerbahce-2-0-%C2%A0fraport-tav-antalyaspor|url-status=live}}</ref> He started getting more playing time as the [[2021–22 Süper Lig|2021–22 season]] progressed.

In March 2022, Güler became Fenerbahçe's youngest goalscorer in Süper Lig history, having just turned 17 three weeks earlier. By May 2022, Güler had scored 3 goals and delivered 3 assists in just 255 minutes of playing time. After an impressive start to his career, it was reported that big European clubs like [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], [[Borussia Dortmund]], [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] and [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] showed their interest in signing him.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Arda Guler: The Turkish wonderkid the whole of Europe wants to sign |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/arda-guler-turkish-wonderkid-whole-europe-want-sign/blt7b158033c7eb2c97 |access-date=18 August 2022 |website=Goal (website) |archive-date=18 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220818083010/https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/arda-guler-turkish-wonderkid-whole-europe-want-sign/blt7b158033c7eb2c97 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Sport |date=6 June 2022 |title=PSG join Barça on the list of clubs that want Arda Guler |url=https://www.sport.es/en/news/barca/psg-join-barca-on-the-list-of-clubs-that-want-arda-guler-13788950 |access-date=18 August 2022 |website=sport |archive-date=18 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718181952/https://www.sport.es/en/news/barca/psg-join-barca-on-the-list-of-clubs-that-want-arda-guler-13788950 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 17 March 2022, Fenerbahçe announced that they had signed a three-year contract with him.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Fenerbahçe Yolunuz Açık Olsun… Armamızla, Uzun Yıllar Nice Başarılara – Fenerbahçe Spor Kulübü |trans-title=Fenerbahçe, May your path be clear... With our emblem, to many successes for many years – Fenerbahçe Sports Club. |url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2022/3/fenerbahce-yolunuz-acik-olsun%E2%80%A6-armamizla-uzun-yillar-nice-basarilara |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220420001221/https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2022/3/fenerbahce-yolunuz-acik-olsun%E2%80%A6-armamizla-uzun-yillar-nice-basarilara |archive-date=20 April 2022 |access-date=28 June 2023}}</ref>

====2022–23 season====
At the start of [[2022–23 Süper Lig|2022–23 season]], after the departure of [[Mesut Özil]], Güler was given the number 10, which has a special meaning for [[Fenerbahçe S.K. supporters|Fenerbahçe fans]], being the number of former players [[Alex (footballer, born 1977)|Alex de Souza]] and [[Jay-Jay Okocha]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 August 2022 |title=Fenerbahçede yeni on numara Arda Güler! |trans-title=Fenerbahçe's new number 10 is Arda Güler! |url=https://www.fanatik.com.tr/fenerbahcede-yeni-on-numara-arda-guler-2295473 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220818083009/https://www.fanatik.com.tr/fenerbahcede-yeni-on-numara-arda-guler-2295473 |archive-date=18 August 2022 |access-date=18 August 2022 |website=Fanatik}}</ref> Güler played his first match of the season against [[Kasımpaşa S.K.|Kasımpaşa]] and scored two goals in 21 minutes of play.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kasımpaşa vs Fenerbahçe (0–6) Aug 15, 2022 Match Stats |url=https://www.footballcritic.com/super-lig-kascmpaca-sk-fenerbahce-sk/match-stats/2726785 |access-date=18 August 2022 |website=FootballCritic |archive-date=18 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718182716/https://www.footballcritic.com/super-lig-kascmpaca-sk-fenerbahce-sk/match-stats/2726785 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 3 November 2022, he scored his first goal in European competitions, and also provided an assist, in a 2–0 away win over [[FC Dynamo Kyiv|Dynamo Kyiv]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League group stage|Europa League group stage]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2035975--dynamo-kyiv-vs-fenerbahce/ |title=Dynamo Kyiv 0–2 Fenerbahçe |publisher=UEFA |date=3 November 2022 |access-date=6 July 2023 |archive-date=24 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221124001121/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2035975--dynamo-kyiv-vs-fenerbahce/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 11 June 2023, Güler put in a [[man of the match]] performance in a 2–0 win at [[2023 Turkish Cup final]] against [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]].<ref name="TCW">{{Cite web |date=11 June 2023 |title=Fenerbahçe-Başakşehir finaline Arda Güler damgası! |trans-title=Arda Güler leaves his mark on the Fenerbahçe-Başakşehir final! |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/fenerbahce-basaksehir-finaline-arda-guler-damgasi-basaksehir-durduramadi-batshuayi-42282354 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230612194101/https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/fenerbahce-basaksehir-finaline-arda-guler-damgasi-basaksehir-durduramadi-batshuayi-42282354 |archive-date=12 June 2023 |access-date=12 June 2023}}</ref> On 6 July, Güler took to [[Instagram]] to announce his departure from Fenerbahçe, marking the end of his tenure with the Turkish club.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Garlan |first=Victor |date=6 July 2023 |title=Arda Güler fait ses adieux au Fenerbahçe |trans-title=Arda Güler bids farewell to Fenerbahçe |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a209661201661605401-arda-guler-fait-ses-adieux-au-fenerbahce |access-date=6 July 2023 |website=Foot Mercato |language=fr |archive-date=5 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231005224303/https://www.footmercato.net/a209661201661605401-arda-guler-fait-ses-adieux-au-fenerbahce |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Real Madrid===
On 6 July 2023, [[La Liga]] club [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] announced the signing of Güler to a six-year contract lasting until June 2029.<ref>{{Cite web |date=6 July 2023 |title=Official Announcement: Arda Güler |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2023/07/06/official-announcement-arda-guler |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230708163819/https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2023/07/06/official-announcement-arda-guler |archive-date=8 July 2023 |access-date=6 July 2023 |website= |publisher=[[Real Madrid CF]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Arda Güler becomes a Real Madrid player |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2023/07/06/arda-guler-becomes-a-real-madrid-player |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230708073345/https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2023/07/06/arda-guler-becomes-a-real-madrid-player |archive-date=8 July 2023 |access-date=6 July 2023 |website= |publisher=Real Madrid CF}}</ref> The deal was sealed by triggering his release clause with an initial payment of €20 million, which surpassed the €17.5 million clause from his former contract with Fenerbahçe.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Real sign Turkish wonderkid Guler from Fenerbahce |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66125179 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718164351/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66125179 |archive-date=18 July 2023 |access-date=6 July 2023 |work= |publisher=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=6 July 2023 |title=Real Madrid beat Barcelona to win race for Turkish wonderkid |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/real-madrid-beat-barcelona-to-win-race-for-turkish-wonderkid-37800934 |access-date=6 July 2023 |website=OneFootball |archive-date=5 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231005224455/https://onefootball.com/en/news/real-madrid-beat-barcelona-to-win-race-for-turkish-wonderkid-37800934 |url-status=live }}</ref> Güler requested Real Madrid to pay beyond his release clause to raise funds for his former club.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Cortegana |first=Mario |title=Arda Guler chooses to join Real Madrid ahead of Barcelona |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4665902/2023/07/04/arda-guler-real-madrid/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718101401/https://theathletic.com/4665902/2023/07/04/arda-guler-real-madrid/ |archive-date=18 July 2023 |access-date=6 July 2023 |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=4 July 2023 |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

====2023–24 season====
Following multiple injuries in late 2023, Güler debuted for Real Madrid in the [[2023–24 Copa del Rey|Copa del Rey]] match against [[Arandina CF|Arandina]] on 6 January 2024,<ref>{{Cite web |date=7 January 2024 |title=Madrid will be patient with Guler after debut, boss Ancelotti says |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/madrid-will-be-patient-with-guler-after-debut-boss-ancelotti-says-2024-01-07/ |access-date=7 January 2024 |website=Reuters |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107120857/https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/madrid-will-be-patient-with-guler-after-debut-boss-ancelotti-says-2024-01-07/ |url-status=live }}</ref> contributing to the team's 3–1 win.<ref>{{Cite web |date=6 January 2024 |title=Madrid book place in Copa del Rey last 16 |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/reports/06-01-2024 |access-date=7 January 2024 |website=Real Madrid C.F. |language=en-US |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107055707/https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/reports/06-01-2024 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=6 January 2024 |title=Atletico, Real win to advance to Spanish Cup last 16, Betis knocked out |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/atletico-real-win-advance-spanish-cup-last-16-betis-knocked-out-2024-01-06/ |access-date=7 January 2024 |website=Reuters}}</ref>
[[File:Modric in LIV VS RMA 2024 (cropped).jpg|thumb|300x300px|Güler (right) playing alongside [[Luka Modrić]] (left) for [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in a [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] match in 2024]]
On 14 January, Güler won his first trophy with Real Madrid in the [[2024 Supercopa de España final|Supercopa de España final]], where Real Madrid triumphed over [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] with a score of 4–1.<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 January 2024 |title=Spanish Super Cup champions! |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/es-ES/en-US/news/football/first-team/reports/14-01-2024 |access-date=15 January 2024 |website=Real Madrid C.F. |language=en-US |archive-date=27 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240127115430/https://www.realmadrid.com/es-ES/en-US/news/football/first-team/reports/14-01-2024 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=14 January 2024 |title=Arda Güler, Real Madrid ile ilk kupasını kazandı! |trans-title=Arda Guler wins his first trophy with Real Madrid! |url=https://beinsports.com.tr/haber/arda-guler-real-madrid-ile-ilk-kupasini-kazandi |access-date=15 January 2024 |website=[[beIN Sports]] |language=tr |archive-date=14 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240114223541/https://beinsports.com.tr/haber/arda-guler-real-madrid-ile-ilk-kupasini-kazandi |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his La Liga debut against [[UD Las Palmas|Las Palmas]] on 27 January, coming on as a substitute in the 81st minute, replacing [[Rodrygo]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 January 2024 |title=Tchouameni grabs Madrid late win at Las Palmas to top Liga |url=https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20240127-tchouameni-grabs-madrid-late-win-at-las-palmas-to-top-liga |access-date=27 January 2024 |website=France 24 |language=en |archive-date=4 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240204112954/https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20240127-tchouameni-grabs-madrid-late-win-at-las-palmas-to-top-liga |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=27 January 2024 |title=Arda Güler sahaya çıktı Real zor da olsa kazandı |trans-title=Arda Guler took the field Real won even if it was difficult |url=https://beinsports.com.tr/haber/arda-guler-sahaya-cikti-real-zor-da-olsa-kazandi |access-date=27 January 2024 |website=beIN Sports |language=tr-TR |archive-date=27 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240127184443/https://beinsports.com.tr/haber/arda-guler-sahaya-cikti-real-zor-da-olsa-kazandi |url-status=live }}</ref> On 10 March, he scored his first league goal for Real Madrid, dribbling past [[RC Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]] goalkeeper [[Vicente Guaita]] in the fourth minute of stoppage time, five minutes after being substituted on, to seal a 4–0 league victory over Celta Vigo.<ref>{{cite web |date=10 March 2024 |title=Real Madrid 4–0 Celta Vigo: Vinicius Junior and Arda Guler score in La Liga win |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/68530327 |access-date=10 March 2024 |website=BBC Sport |archive-date=4 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240404000809/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/68530327 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Arda Güler: "I'm thrilled to have scored my first goal" |date=10 March 2024 |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/el-primer-gol-de-arda-guler-con-el-real-madrid-regate-y-definicion-10-03-2024 |access-date=11 March 2024 |publisher=Real Madrid CF |archive-date=2 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240402112129/https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/el-primer-gol-de-arda-guler-con-el-real-madrid-regate-y-definicion-10-03-2024 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 26 April, Güler marked his first La Liga start with a goal in a 1–0 win against [[Real Sociedad]] at [[Anoeta Stadium|Reale Arena]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 April 2024 |title=Real Sociedad 0–1 Real Madrid: Arda Güler scores as Real Madrid close in on title |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68909689 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240426225742/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68909689 |archive-date=26 April 2024 |access-date=26 April 2024 |work=BBC Sport |publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=26 April 2024 |title=Arda Güler: "Me siento muy contento por marcar y por la victoria" |trans-title=Arda Güler: "I'm very happy that I scored and I'm very happy for the win" |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/arda-guler-26-04-2024 |access-date=27 April 2024 |publisher=Real Madrid CF |language=es |archive-date=17 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240517111228/https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/arda-guler-26-04-2024/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 19 May, he scored a brace against [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] in a 4–4 draw, becoming the fastest player in Real Madrid's history to score six La Liga goals in just 330 minutes&nbsp;of playing time.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 May 2024 |title="Turkish Messi", "This kid is unreal" – Fans hail Arda Guler for his performance in Real Madrid's 4–4 draw against Villarreal |url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/news-turkish-messi-this-kid-unreal-fans-hail-arda-guler-performance-real-madrid-s-4-4-draw-villarreal |access-date=24 May 2024 |work=sportskeeda |language=en |archive-date=24 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240524141424/https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/news-turkish-messi-this-kid-unreal-fans-hail-arda-guler-performance-real-madrid-s-4-4-draw-villarreal |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=19 May 2024 |title=Arda Güler continues ridiculous start to Madrid career |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/arda-gueler-continues-ridiculous-start-to-madrid-career-39513294 |access-date=24 May 2024 |work=onefootball |language=en}}</ref> Although he did not play in the competition, he became the first Turkish player to win the [[UEFA Champions League]] when his club clinched their 15th title with a 2–0 win over [[Borussia Dortmund]] in the [[2024 UEFA Champions League final|final]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dailysabah.com/sports/football/turkish-star-guler-breaks-new-ground-as-madrid-bag-15th-ucl-title |title=Turkish star Güler breaks new ground as Madrid bag 15th UCL title |work=Daily Sabah |date=2 June 2024 }}</ref>

====2024–25 season====
Güler made his Champions League debut as a substitute in the opening match of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|league phase]], which ended in a 3–1 victory over [[VfB Stuttgart|Stuttgart]] on 17 September 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/not-normal-arda-g-ler-185900233.html |title='Not normal' – Arda Güler hails Real Madrid teammate after win over Stuttgart |publisher=Yahoo Sports |date=18 September 2024 }}</ref> Later that year, he scored his first goal of the season in a 3–0 away win over [[Girona FC|Girona]] in [[2024–25 La Liga|La Liga]] on 7 December.<ref>{{Cite web |date=7 December 2024 |title=Arda Güler: "We ran a lot, we battled hard and we're extremely pleased to have won convincingly" |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/arda-guler-07-12-2024 |access-date=9 December 2024 |publisher=Real Madrid CF |language=en}}</ref> After being used mainly in [[Copa del Rey]] matches and seeing limited time in league games for most part of the season, Güler was given rare back-to-back league starts on 23 April 2025 when he scored the winner and was nominated player of the match in a 1–0 win over [[Getafe CF|Getafe]], and on 4 May when he registered a goal and an assist in a 3–2 victory over Celta Vigo.<ref>{{Cite web |date=28 April 2025 |title=Arda Güler: The Light in the Darkness for Real Madrid's End of Season |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/la-liga/articles-video/arda-güler-the-light-in-the-darkness-for-real-madrid-s-end-of-season-2025-04-27 |access-date=5 May 2025 |publisher=[[beinsports.com]] |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=4 May 2025 |title=Arda Güler Shines in Real Madrid's Win Over Celta |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/la-liga/articles-video/arda-güler-shines-in-real-madrid-s-win-over-celta-2025-05-04 |access-date=5 May 2025 |publisher=[[beinsports.com]] |language=en}}</ref>

====2025–26 season====
Following [[Xabi Alonso]]'s appointment as Real Madrid head coach, Güler began featuring more regularly in the starting lineup, primarily in a midfield role. On 30 August 2025, he netted his first goal of the season in a 2–1 La Liga win over [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]], putting in a man-of-the-match performance.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Real Madrid youngster considered 'special' by Xabi Alonso; set for a prominent role |url=https://www.madriduniversal.com/real-madrid-youngster-considered-special-by-xabi-alonso-set-for-a-prominent-role/ |date=6 August 2025 |access-date=1 September 2025 |publisher=Madrid Universal |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=31 August 2025 |title=Real Madrid player ratings vs Mallorca: Vinicius Jr and Arda Guler to the rescue! Los Blancos complete lightning-quick LaLiga comeback as Xabi Alonso's side see three goals ruled out |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/real-madrid-player-ratings-vs-mallorca-vinicius-jr-arda-guler-xabi-alonso/blt5505194e83b14169#cs857f06d8140af4e2 |access-date=1 September 2025 |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |language=en}}</ref> Throughout August and September, Güler began to play an increasingly important role in Real Madrid’s squad, earning consistent starts. His performances culminated in being named the La Liga U23 Player of the Month for September, having scored two goals and provided two assists during that period.<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 September 2025 |title=Arda Güler, LALIGA EA SPORTS U23 Player of the Month for September 25/26 |url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/news/arda-guler-laliga-ea-sports-u23-player-of-the-month-for-september-25-26 |access-date=1 October 2025 |website=Página web oficial de LALIGA {{!}} LALIGA |language=en}}</ref>

On 14 March 2026, he scored a 68-meter goal from his own half in a 4–1 victory over&nbsp;[[Elche CF|Elche]], setting a new record for the longest goal ever scored in La Liga, tying the mark set by [[José Antonio Culebras|Antonio José]] in 2004 from a very similar distance.The goal was later named La Liga Goal of the Season.<ref>{{cite news|date=3 June 2026|title=Arda Güler, LALIGA EA SPORTS Goal of the Season 2025/26 |url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/news/arda-guler-laliga-ea-sports-goal-of-the-season-2025-26 |website=LALIGA Official Website |access-date=4 June 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=15 March 2026 |title=How far was Arda Güler’s goal in Real Madrid vs Elche? |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/la-liga/articles/how-far-was-arda-g%C3%BCler-s-goal-in-real-madrid-vs-elche-2026-03-14-untitled_content_item_79aefed |access-date=16 March 2026 |publisher=beIN SPORTS |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/news/real-madrid-score-screamer-halfway-220300230.html |title=Real Madrid score a screamer from before the halfway line |publisher=Yahoo! Sports |date=14 March 2026 }}</ref> A month later, on 15 April, Güler scored his first Champions League goals, including the club's fastest-ever goal in the competition after 34 seconds, breaking previous record of [[Felo (footballer, born 1936)|Felo]] in 1962,<ref>{{cite web |last=Lopez Vega |first=Alejandro |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/sports/soccer/arda-guler-s-34-second-goal-ranks-13th-among-the-fastest-in-champions-league-history-who-s-no-1/ar-AA20Z4GY |title=Arda Guler’s 34-second goal ranks 13th among the fastest in Champions League history: Who’s No. 1? |publisher=MSN |date=15 April 2026 }}</ref> before adding another from a free-kick, giving his side the lead on two separate occasions in a 4–3 away defeat against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|quarter-finals]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/02a4-2065d3ad61f5-d3ad2c2b1ca9-1000--bayern-munchen-4-3-real-madrid-agg-6-4-late-goals-send-baye/ |title=Bayern München 4-3 Real Madrid (agg: 6-4): Late goals send Bayern to semi-finals in Champions League classic |publisher=UEFA |date=15 April 2026 }}</ref> In addition, he was shown a red card after the final whistle for protesting the sending-off of his teammate, [[Eduardo Camavinga]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Riley |first=Martha |url=https://talksport.com/football/4188342/jude-bellingham-pulled-away-official-arda-guler-red-card-chaos/ |title=Jude Bellingham pulled away from referee and Real Madrid teammate sent off after full-time in chaotic scenes |publisher=talkSPORT |date=15 April 2026 }}</ref> At the conclusion of the tournament, he was awarded the Champions League’s Young Player of the Season honor.<ref>{{cite web |last=Arora |first=Hridyam |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/articles/official-arda-g-ler-named-160255834.html |title=OFFICIAL: Arda Güler named UCL Young Player of the Season |publisher=Yahoo! Sports |date=31 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Güler is a Turkish youth international, having played up to the [[Turkey national under-21 football team|Turkey U21]]s. He made his senior international debut for [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] on 19 November 2022, in their 2–1 friendly win against [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]]. He scored his first goal against [[Wales national football team|Wales]] in [[Euro 2024 qualifiers]] on 19 June 2023.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Wales' Euro hopes in tatters after defeat in Turkey |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65874635 |access-date=20 June 2023 |archive-date=23 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230623122113/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65874635 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===UEFA Euro 2024===
Güler was named in Turkey's 26-man squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=A Millî Takımımızın EURO 2024 Aday Kadrosu Açıklandı |trans-title=EURO 2024 Candidate Squad of Our National Team Announced |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |language=tr |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |access-date=18 June 2024 |archive-date=7 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240607205837/https://tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 18 June 2024, he was awarded Player of the Match, as he scored in Turkey's 3–1 opening fixture win over [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]], becoming the first teenager to score on his [[UEFA European Championship|European Championship]] debut since [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] in [[UEFA Euro 2004|2004]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028e-1b29ce033a7b-f0319eea90ab-1000--turkiye-3-1-georgia-arda-guler-thunderbolt-settles-thrillin/ |title=Türkiye 3–1 Georgia: Arda Güler thunderbolt lights up thrilling win |work=[[UEFA]] |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |date=18 June 2024 |access-date=18 June 2024 |archive-date=18 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240618182854/https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028e-1b29ce033a7b-f0319eea90ab-1000--turkiye-3-1-georgia-arda-guler-thunderbolt-settles-thrillin/ |url-status=live }}</ref> With his goal, he also became the fifth-youngest goalscorer in the tournament's history and the youngest debutant to find the net, aged 19 years and 114 days, breaking Cristiano Ronaldo's previous record.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028e-1b131a1d2848-526b6661948b-1000--euro-s-youngest-scorers-vonlanthen-rooney-renato-sanches-/ |title=EURO's youngest scorers: Vonlanthen, Rooney, Renato Sanches, Stojković, Arda Güler |work=[[UEFA]] |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |date=18 June 2024 |access-date=18 June 2024 |archive-date=18 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240618182854/https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028e-1b131a1d2848-526b6661948b-1000--euro-s-youngest-scorers-vonlanthen-rooney-renato-sanches-/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Fretton |first=Mitchell |url=https://www.goal.com/en-kw/lists/arda-guler-breaks-cristiano-ronaldo-record-turkish-messi-incredible-goal-euro-2024-win-georgia/bltdfa72a2c5b29953a#cs08cf7c8af8303a8c |title=Arda Guler breaks long-standing Cristiano Ronaldo record as 'Turkish Messi' scores incredible goal in Euro 2024 win over Georgia |publisher=Goal.com |date=18 June 2024 |access-date=18 June 2024 |archive-date=18 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240618183252/https://www.goal.com/en-kw/lists/arda-guler-breaks-cristiano-ronaldo-record-turkish-messi-incredible-goal-euro-2024-win-georgia/bltdfa72a2c5b29953a#cs08cf7c8af8303a8c |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 3 July, Güler provided an assist as Turkey defeated [[Austria national football team|Austria]] 2–1 in the round of 16 and progressed into the quarter-finals. In doing so, he became only the third teenager in history to score and assist in the same Euros, following&nbsp;Cristiano Ronaldo&nbsp;and&nbsp;[[Wayne Rooney]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2 July 2024 |title=Arda Guler joins Cristiano Ronaldo and Wayne Rooney in exclusive European Championship club |url=https://talksport.com/football/1947574/arda-guler-cristiano-ronaldo-wayne-rooney-euro-2024/ |access-date=3 July 2024 |publisher=talksport |language=en}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Considered by various media outlets and commentators to be one of the best young footballers in the world,<ref name=":2">{{cite web |date=1 July 2024 |title=The 25 best young players in world football right now ranked in order |url=https://www.givemesport.com/best-young-players-in-world-football-soccer-ranked/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240710230933/https://www.givemesport.com/best-young-players-in-world-football-soccer-ranked/ |archive-date=10 July 2024 |access-date=10 July 2024 |website=Give Me Sport}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{cite web |date=4 September 2024 |title=2024 Kopa Trophy Nominees Announced: Lamine Yamal, Arda Güler... |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/premier-league/articles-video/2024-kopa-trophy-nominees-announced-lamine-yamal-arda-güler-2024-09-04 |access-date=25 September 2024 |website=beinsports}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{cite web |date=10 July 2024 |title=FRANCISCO CONCEICAO, ARDA GULER, LAMINE YAMAL: WHO ARE THE BEST YOUNG PLAYERS IN THE EUROPEAN CHAMPIONSHIP? |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/euro/2024/francisco-conceicao-arda-guler-lamine-yamal-who-are-the-best-young-players-in-the-european-championship_sto20011878/story.shtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240618212204/https://www.eurosport.com/football/euro/2024/francisco-conceicao-arda-guler-lamine-yamal-who-are-the-best-young-players-in-the-european-championship_sto20011878/story.shtml |archive-date=18 June 2024 |access-date=13 July 2024 |website=eurosport.com}}</ref><ref name=":5">{{Cite web |last=Ramsay |first=George |date=22 June 2024 |title=How 19-year-old Arda Güler, dubbed 'the Turkish Messi,' lit up the European Championship |url=https://www.cnn.com/2024/06/22/sport/arda-guler-profile-euro-2024-turkey-spt-intl |access-date=18 July 2025 |website=CNN |language=en}}</ref> Güler is a left-footed [[attacking midfielder]] who can also play as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]], primarily on the right flank. He has been praised for his composure and ability to operate in tight spaces. A [[playmaker]], Güler has also been noted for his impressive dribbling skill, vision, creativity, above-average passing skills, and technical ability from set-pieces.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last=Aschi |first=Léo |date=18 March 2024 |title=Who is Real Madrid and Turkey wonderkid Arda Guler |url=https://www.givemesport.com/real-madrid-arda-guler-player-profile-ancelotti/ |access-date=18 April 2025 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref>

